Naftna Industrija Srbije AD (NIIS) , the
Serbian oil and gas company controlled by  OAO Gazprom Neft (GAZP) , will
invest $25 million in equipment for its oilfield services unit.  The Novi Sad, Serbia-based company bought three drilling
sets for $7.5 million as well as equipment for geological
surveys from Sercel, a unit of  CGGVeritas (GA) , the worldâ€™s largest
